In a large saucepan, combine the pie filling, blackberries and cinnamon. Cook over medium heat until mixture is bubbly, stirring occasionally. Pour into a greased 11-in.x 7-in.x 2-in. baking dish. In a small bowl, combine the sugar and cinnamon. Dip biscuits in butter and then in cinnamon-sugar. Arrange biscuits around edges of dish; sprinkle with almonds. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.